list_page_teaser: The image of each of the Sixteen Types has its own unique characteristics.  Learn how the Groja program constructs the image of each of these types.
description_html:
This gallery contains a generic image of each of the Sixteen Types.

They are in alphabetical order, and the preference ratio used in all images is 58% to 42%. This makes all the images quite colorful, while solidly expressing the personality's preferences.

Although we should all be proud of who we are, I strongly believe that we should never think for a second that one type is 'better' than another!
story_html:
Generic images portray a personality with preferences that are a fixed percentage. For example, the score used to generate the generic image of an ISTP in this gallery is E:42%/I:58%, N:42%/S:58%, F:42%/T:58%, and J:42%/P:58%.

This gallery contains a generic image of each of the sixteen types. Note however, that real people do not always look so balanced!

They are in alphabetical order, and the preference ratio used in all images is 58% to 42%. This makes all the images quite colorful, while solidly expressing the personality's preferences.

Although we should all be proud of who we are, I strongly believe that we should never think for a second that one type is 'better' than another!

image_list.title: ENFJ
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ENFJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Red lines in this image represent the ENFJ's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their warmth causes them to seek harmonious relationships and enables them to make strong social connections.  This Extraverted Feeling makes ENFJs outgoing, polite, friendly, charming, and loyal.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter horizontal Blue lines represent the ENFJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Introverted iNtuition.  Their openness to new ideas gives them the ability to reconcile seemingly contradictory evidence and gain sudden insight - an 'Aha!' moment - into future possibilities.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an ENFJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of ENFJ personality types.

image_list.title: ENFP
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ENFP using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Blue lines in this image represent the ENFP's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted iNtuition.  Their openness causes them to explore alternatives and find hidden possibilities.  This Extraverted iNtuition makes ENFPs perceptive, charismatic, versatile, clever, and enthusiastic about making things happen.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter horizontal Red lines represent the ENFP's Auxiliary personality trait, their Introverted Feeling.  Their desire for authenticity and inner harmony can give them 'gut feelings' when it comes to discerning the finer distinctions between good and bad, and truth and falsehood.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an ENFP is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of ENFP personality types.

image_list.title: ENTJ
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ENTJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Green lines in this image represent the ENTJ's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted Thinking.  Their ability to reason logically enables them to organize their environment and schedule events to efficiently produce results.  This Extraverted Thinking makes ENTJs analytical and decisive.  They value truth, seek logical explanations, work well in organizations, and can make excellent leaders.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter horizontal Blue lines represent the ENTJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Introverted iNtuition.  Their openness to new ideas gives them the ability to reconcile seemingly contradictory evidence and gain sudden insight - an 'Aha!' moment - into future possibilities.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an ENTJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of ENTJ personality types.

image_list.title: ENTP
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ENTP using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Blue lines in this image represent the ENTP's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted iNtuition.  Their openness causes them to explore alternatives and find hidden possibilities.  This Extraverted iNtuition makes ENTPs perceptive, charismatic, versatile, clever, and enthusiastic about making things happen.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter horizontal Green lines represent the ENTP's Auxiliary personality trait, their Introverted Thinking.  Their ability to reason, categorize, and analyze ideas and things enables them to solve problems efficiently and can compel them to figure out how things work.

image_list.title: ESFJ
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ESFJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long vertical Red lines in this image represent the ESFJ's Dominant personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their warmth causes them to seek harmonious relationships and enables them to make strong social connections.  This Extraverted Feeling makes ESFJs outgoing, polite, friendly, considerate, and loyal.

image_list.title: INFJ
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an INFJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Blue lines in this image represent the INFJ's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted iNtuition.  Their inner vision makes them insightful, ingenious, and individualistic.  This Introverted iNtuition makes INFJs driven, inspired, and determined.  When properly motivated, they can overcome difficulties and find new paths in any field they choose.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Red lines represent the INFJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their desire for warm, harmonious relationships makes them tactful, polite, and open to what others want.  They are conscientious, sensitive and loyal, and radiate warmth.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an INFJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of INFJ personality types.

image_list.title: INFP
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an INFP using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Red lines in this image represent the INFP's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted Feeling.  Their deep passion for inner harmony rarely surfaces, and an inner morality or 'gut feeling' takes precedence, so the opinions of others may matter little.  This Introverted Feeling makes INFPs idealistic, authentic and faithful, and gives them a strong sense of duty.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Blue lines represent the INFP's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted iNtuition.  Their openness to others' thoughts, experiences, ideas, and feelings makes them a source of inspiration and enthusiastic about pursuing all sorts of different possibilities.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an INFP is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of INFP personality types.

image_list.title: INTJ
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an INTJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Blue lines in this image represent the INTJ's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted iNtuition.  Their inner vision makes them insightful, ingenious, and individualistic.  This Introverted iNtuition makes INTJs driven, inspired, and determined.  When properly motivated, they can overcome difficulties and find new paths in any field they choose.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Green lines represent the INTJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted Thinking.  They are analytical, decisive, and strive to make things more efficient. They value the truth and enjoy taking charge by scheduling and organizing the time they spend with others.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an INTJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of INTJ personality types.

image_list.title: INTP
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an INTP using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Green lines in this image represent the INTP's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted Thinking.  Their impersonal analysis of concepts and facts can make them seem shy and aloof.  This Introverted Thinking makes INTPs quiet, curious, adaptable, perceptive, and interested in finding underlying principles.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Blue lines represent the INTP's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted iNtuition. image_list.title: ISFJ
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ISFJ using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Yellow lines in this image represent the ISFJ's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted Sensation.  Their practical perceptions and deeply stored impressions make them protective of all things they find familiar.  This Introverted Sensation makes ISFJs systematic, responsible, hard-working, and adaptable to routine.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Red lines represent the ISFJ's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted Feeling.  Their desire for warm, harmonious relationships makes them tactful, polite, and open to what others want.  They are conscientious, sensitive and loyal, and radiate warmth.
image_list.story_html: This generic image of an ISFJ is based on fixed percentages and is not an image of any person, real or fictional. This image exists solely to demonstrate the overall appearance of ISFJ personality types.

image_list.title: ISFP
image_list.subtitle_html: Image of an ISFP using fixed percentages.
image_list.explain_dom: The long horizontal Red lines in this image represent the ISFP's Dominant personality trait, their Introverted Feeling.  Their deep passion for inner harmony rarely surfaces, and an inner morality or 'gut feeling' takes precedence, so the opinions of others may matter little.  This Introverted Feeling makes ISFPs authentic, faithful, idealistic, and gives them a strong sense of duty.
image_list.explain_aux: The shorter vertical Yellow lines represent the ISFP's Auxiliary personality trait, their Extraverted Sensation.
